  <Subject Subject_ID="300228086">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300228728</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>conditions and effects for wood [300228728], conditions and effects by specific type [300389722], Conditions and Effects (hierarchy name) [300186269], Physical Attributes Facet [300264087]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A decay of wood caused by fungus that attacks both cellulose and lignin; the resultant mass is spongy or stringy, usually white, but sometimes yellow, tan, or light brown.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000040381/Panshin and de Zeeuw, Textbook of Wood Technology (1980)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Una descomposición de la madera causada por hongos que atacan a la celulosa y la lignina; la masa resultante es esponjosa o fibrosa, usualmente blanca, pero algunas veces amarillenta o café claro.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een vorm van houtrot die wordt veroorzaakt door schimmels die zowel de cellulose als de lignine aantasten; de massa die hierdoor ontstaat is sponzig of draderig, meestal wit, maar soms geel, geelbruin of lichtbruin.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052554/Houtverduurzaming (1966)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>真菌侵襲纖維素及木質素所引起的木材腐爛，其產生的大量物質呈海綿狀或具黏性，通常為白色，但有時候為黃色、黃褐色或淺棕色。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
